      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. I want to make sure the post doesn't sound like it's just ignoring obvious counter-arguments. People always bring up things like \"protecting children\" or \"preventing hate speech\" as reasons to regulate. How would someone from a libertarian perspective effectively dismantle those specific justifications?",
